{{Quote|All hail the Mysterious Stranger, the greatest duelist to ever grace the rings of Taris!|Duel announcer after Revan kills Bendak Starkiller|<ref name="KoTOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref>}}
The '''"Mysterious Stranger"''' was a nickname given to [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] by [[Ajuur]] the Hutt when he participated in the dueling tournament on [[Taris/Legends|Taris]] held within the [[Taris dueling ring]] in one of the [[Upper City]]'s [[Upper City Cantina|cantina]].

The name was inspired by Revan's current lack of history on that [[Planet/Legends|world]], having only just come to the planetary city in the wake of his and [[Carth Onasi]]'s escape from the [[Attack on the Endar Spire|attack]] on the ''[[Endar Spire]]''. Revan, with a reprogrammed identity, preferred to compete under his presumed birth name, but Ajuur thought that "Mysterious Stranger" sounded much better; in addition, Carth suggested this anonymity in case the [[Darth Revan's Sith Empire|Sith forces]] occupying Taris had come upon a crew manifest aboard the Endar Spire before its destruction. As the Mysterious Stranger, Revan would go on to fight and defeat [[Deadeye Duncan]], [[Gerlon Two-Fingers]], [[Ice (duelist)|Ice]], [[Marl]] and then [[Twitch (Rodian)|Twitch]]. Once he won that fight he was named Taris Dueling Champion and was deemed worthy of a duel to the death by [[Gorse Bendak|Bendak Starkiller]].<ref name="KoTOR" />

The "Mysterious Stranger" nickname reappeared hundreds of years later when the [[Alliance Commander]], participating in the [[Arena Grand|Eternal Championship]], was given the nickname by [[Dominaire]].<ref name="TOR">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic: Knights of the Fallen Empire]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Though it comes from a [[canon]]ical source, the dueling sequence is an optional sidequest within the game ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''. The player does not have to compete in the events there; in addition, dueling Starkiller to the death is also a [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] option and therefore, perhaps non-canon.

The player can give his character any name they like, however plot-wise, Ajuur always insists that the player duels under the moniker 'Mysterious Stranger' as more 'catchy'; this is because the announcer's voice (during the duels) is pre-recorded, thus making the use of a custom name impossible. In the German version, Revan is called "Mysterio" instead of "Mysterious Stranger".

In a scene cut from the final version of the game, Revan may encounter Deadeye Duncan on the planet [[Manaan/Legends|Manaan]]. After learning that his opponent was a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], Duncan asks for permission to use the "Mysterious Stranger" alias for himself to increase his reputation and the player would have the option to accept or refuse.

